  "content": "  <div style=\"font-size: 24px; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.5; margin-bottom: 24px;\">\n    A few days ago I moved to Linux for engineering. The benefits were clear. Now the real test.\n  </div>\n  <!-- Simple CSS monitor illustration -->\n  <div style=\"display: flex; justify-content: center; margin-top: 8px;\">\n    <div style=\"position: relative;\">\n      <!-- Screen -->\n      <div style=\"width: 480px; height: 200px; background: #0d1117; border: 3px solid #475569; border-radius: 12px 12px 0 0; padding: 20px; position: relative; overflow: hidden;\">\n        <!-- Terminal lines -->\n        <div style=\"display: flex; gap: 8px; align-items: center; margin-bottom: 10px;\">\n          <div style=\"width: 8px; height: 8px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--accent-green);\"></div>\n          <div style=\"height: 3px; width: 140px; background: var(--accent-green); opacity: 0.4; border-radius: 2px;\"></div>\n        </div>\n        <div style=\"display: flex; gap: 8px; align-items: center; margin-bottom: 10px;\">\n          <div style=\"width: 8px; height: 8px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--accent-blue);\"></div>\n          <div style=\"height: 3px; width: 100px; background: var(--accent-blue); opacity: 0.4; border-radius: 2px;\"></div>\n        </div>\n        <div style=\"display: flex; gap: 8px; align-items: center;\">\n          <div style=\"width: 8px; height: 8px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--accent-green);\"></div>\n          <div style=\"height: 3px; width: 120px; background: var(--accent-green); opacity: 0.4; border-radius: 2px;\"></div>\n        </div>\n        <!-- DaVinci Resolve overlay -->\n        <div style=\"position: absolute; bottom: 16px; right: 20px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px; background: rgba(239,68,68,0.1); border: 1px solid rgba(239,68,68,0.25); border-radius: 8px; padding: 8px 14px;\">\n          <span style=\"font-size: 24px;\">🎬</span>\n          <span style=\"font-siz